image size 25763 does not match element size 1, depth 3, width 299, height 299

if I manually pass this segment (commenting out the check), I will have either small data, or, data overflow and lose adb connection everytime I execute it:

1,0.000000,1,kit fox

3,0.000000,3,Siberian husky

body:
OK. @satok16, could you at least help me out to pass the image mismatch issue that I am getting by executing the nnlib test app (graph_app). This happens both with `SDK 3.0` and `SDK 3.3.3`. Looking at the code, no matter what parameters I pass, I am stuck with this issue:

`image size 25763 does not match element size 1, depth 3, width 299, height 299`

if I manually pass this segment (commenting out the check), I will have either small data, or, data overflow and lose adb connection everytime I execute it:

```
image size 25763 does not match element size 1, depth 3, width 92, height 92, elements 25763, area 8587
 filesize=25763 elementsize=1 height=92 width=92 depth=3
Run!
execute got err: -1
hexagon/ops/src/op_output.c:59:output 0 too small
Rank,Softmax,index,string
0,0.000000,1023,OVERFLOW!
1,0.000000,1,kit fox
2,0.000000,2,English setter
3,0.000000,3,Siberian husky
4,0.000000,4,Australian terrier
```

What is the correct `weight`, `width`, `depth` and `elements` parameters to be used with `keyboard_299x299.jpg`. Thanks.
